Evaluation of Postfix Expression
An expression is a combination of operands and operators.
In postfix expression (also called Reverse Polish Notation), the operator comes after the operands.
 Example
Copy code

Infix   : (5 + 3) * 2
Postfix : 5 3 + 2 *
ðŸ”¹ Why Postfix Expression?
No need for brackets
No operator precedence problem
Easy evaluation using stack
ðŸ§  Algorithm for Evaluation of Postfix Expression
Initialize an empty stack.
Scan the postfix expression from left to right.
If the symbol is an operand, push it onto the stack.
If the symbol is an operator:
Pop two operands from the stack.
Apply the operator (operand1 operator operand2).
Push the result back onto the stack.
After complete scanning, the top of the stack contains the final result.
ðŸ“‹ Example Evaluation
Postfix Expression:
Copy code

23*54*+9-
Steps:
Copy code

2 3 * â†’ 6
5 4 * â†’ 20
6 + 20 â†’ 26
26 - 9 â†’ 17
Final Result:
Copy code

17
ðŸ”¹ Applications
Used in compilers
Used in expression evaluation
Used in calculators
Used in stack-based systems

#include <stdio.h>
#include <ctype.h>

#define MAX 50

int stack[MAX];
int top = -1;

/* Push operation */
void push(int value) {
    stack[++top] = value;
}

/* Pop operation */
int pop() {
    return stack[top--];
}

/* Main function */
int main() {
    char postfix[MAX];
    int i, op1, op2, result;

    printf("Enter Postfix Expression: ");
    scanf("%s", postfix);

    for (i = 0; postfix[i] != '\0'; i++) {

        /* If operand, push to stack */
        if (isdigit(postfix[i])) {
            push(postfix[i] - '0');
        }
        /* If operator */
        else {
            op2 = pop();
            op1 = pop();

            switch (postfix[i]) {
                case '+': result = op1 + op2; break;
                case '-': result = op1 - op2; break;
                case '*': result = op1 * op2; break;
                case '/': result = op1 / op2; break;
            }
            push(result);
        }
    }

    printf("Result = %d\n", pop());
    return 0;
}
input
23*54*+9-
output 
Result = 17
